.TH cran2crux 1 "May 2026"

.SH NAME
cran2crux \- generate CRUX ports for R packages from CRAN and Bioconductor

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cran2crux
.RI "[options]"
.RI "[package]"
.RI "[depth]"

.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fIcran2crux\fP script automatically generates ready-to-use port(s) for
R packages available from CRAN (\fIhttps://cran.r-project.org/\fP) and
Bioconductor (\fIhttps://bioconductor.org/\fP). 

The script creates ports in the current working directory, which must be empty.
Each generated port is named \fBr4-foo\fP (lowercase) and has release number 1.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B "\-r, \-\-recursive"
Create a port for an R package and recursively create ports for its dependencies.

.TP
.B "\-ro, \-\-recursive\-opt"
Create a port for an R package and recursively create ports for its dependencies
as well as its optional dependencies. This may require setting a higher
dependency depth (see below). This option is slow and its usage is discouraged.

.TP
.B "\-so, \-\-show\-old"
Check for potential updates of already installed R packages. Reports versions
found in the upstream repositories.

.TP
.B "\-u, \-\-update"
Generate updated ports for installed R packages that have newer versions available.

.TP
.B "\-h, \-\-help"
Display help and exit.

.TP
.B "<dependencies depth>"
A positive integer supplied after the \fB\-r\fP or \fB\-ro\fP option. It defines
how many iterations of recursive dependency searches will be performed.
Use higher values (>10) when the dependency list is expected to be large.

.SH CONFIG
You should configure \fI/etc/cran2crux.conf\fP to set the maintainer line,
CRAN mirror, Bioconductor mirror, and Bioconductor version. The file uses R syntax:

.PP
.nf
    maintainer.info <- c("Petar Petrov, slackalaxy at gmail dot com")
    cranrepo.url <- "https://cloud.r-project.org"
    bioc.url     <- "https://bioconductor.org/packages/"
    bioc.version <- "3.23"
.fi

.SH EXAMPLES

Call \fIcran2crux\fP in a newly created, empty directory:

.PP
.nf
    mkdir rports
    cd rports
.fi

.PP
This will create a port for an R-package:

.PP
.nf
    cran2crux Foo
.fi

.PP
This will create a port for Foo and dependencies recursively:

.PP
.nf
    cran2crux Foo -r
.fi

.PP
This will create a port for Foo, its dependencies and optional
dependencies, recursively. This may require more intensive dependency
searches, therefore we increase the depth value to 15:

.PP
.nf
    cran2crux Foo -ro 15
.fi

.PP
This will show potential updates of installed R-packages:

.PP
.nf
    cran2crux -so
.fi

.PP
This will generate updated ports for outdated R-packages already installed:

.PP
.nf
    cran2crux -u
.fi

.SH AUTHOR
\fIcran2crux\fP was written by Petar Petrov <slackalaxy@gmail.com> for CRUX.
